  "description": "It\u0026rsquo;s hard not to be disappointed in myself for not taking oodles of screenshots and recordings of every conversation I\u0026rsquo;ve had on the Web with folk, because I definitely remember getting into contentious arguments with @Cyborgneticz@scholars.social about all sorts of stuff, generally focused around how directly to support antagonism of colonialism, and the risks around doing it for the marginalized. That is, they\u0026rsquo;d argue being queer is a risk, thus asking for greater antagonism is asking too much, and I\u0026rsquo;d argue that there are queers who aren\u0026rsquo;t white settlers that are antagonising things, and their stance, while fine to personally hold, presented as a truth, erases those people and those efforts.\n",
